dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks compared to CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: TinyImageNet is a dataset that contains 100,000 training images and 10,000 validation images across 200 classes, with each image having a resolution of 64x64 pixels. It is used for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: TinyImageNet

dcterms:creator: Tzu-Ming Harry Hsu
Hang Qi
Matthew Brown
dcterms:description: Dirichlet-µ is a dataset used to measure the effects of non-identical data distribution for federated visual classification, focusing on the heterogeneity of data across clients.
dcterms:title: Dirichlet-µ

dcterms:creator: Tzu-Ming Harry Hsu
Hang Qi
Matthew Brown
dcterms:description: Pathological-n (Path(n)) is a dataset used in federated learning to analyze the effects of non-identical data distribution across clients, focusing on the number of data categories per client.
dcterms:title: Pathological-n (Path(n))
